I was able to reproduce the problem starting from a working, 

nearly-default configuration and substituting 

BucketQueueAssignmentPolicy via the web UI&#39;s &#39;details&#39; option for the 

&#39;root: .



The problem appears to be that the definition of certain shared modules 

by name inside the root map -- specifically &#39;queue-assignment-policy&#39; 

and then &#39;server-cache&#39; -- is in a problematic order once a 

BucketQueueAssignmentPolicy is introduced.



The &#39;queue-assignment-policy&#39; comes first and unlike other policies, 

BucketQueueAssignmentPolicy needs a reference to a ServerCache. There 

should only be one ServerCache, so an instance is created there, and all 

later ServerCache references should refer back to it. However, the 

immediately following &#39;server-cache&#39; definition inside the &#39;root&#39; map 

can&#39;t be filled by autowire references, as the exception indicates.



I&#39;m not certain if that&#39;s a truly necessary restriction, but a 

workaround that removed the problem for me was to ensure that the 

&#39;root:server-cache&#39; definition comes right before, rather than right 

after, &#39;root:queue-assignment-policy&#39;.



This can&#39;t be done via the web UI; I did it in the on-disk global.sheet 

before attempting to swap in BucketQueueAssignmentPolicy.



A small test crawl with BucketQueueAssignmentPolicy then launched and 

completed.



Hope this helps,



- Gordon @ IA



